text: Paracapperia esuriens is a moth of the family Pterophoridae that is known from Ethiopia, the Democratic Republic of the Congo and Angola. ==References== Category:Oxyptilini Category:Moths described in 1932 Category:Insects of the Democratic Republic of the Congo Category:Insects of Angola Category:Insects of Ethiopia Category:Moths of Africa Category:Taxa named by Edward Meyrick
title: Paracapperia esuriens
